      <h2 id="special-thoughts-on-healing-after-losing-a-pet">Special Thoughts on Healing After Losing a Pet</h2>
      <p></p>
<p>Healing takes time; your words can offer hope and reassurance.</p>
<p>The pain of losing a pet is immense, but remember that the love you shared will endure.  Take your time to grieve, and know that healing is possible.  Allow yourself to feel your emotions, and remember the joy your cat brought into your life.</p>
<p>Though the emptiness left by your cat's absence may feel overwhelming right now, remember the incredible bond you shared, the unconditional love you received, and the lasting impact your cat had on your life.  Cherish those memories and know that their spirit lives on within you.  Healing takes time, be patient with yourself, and allow those around you to support you.  In time, the joy and love you experienced will soften the sorrow.</p>
    
  
